File: The wide-ranging documents allow delegates to discuss issues affecting the governing party ahead of the crucial meeting. AFP/Marco Longari JOHANNESBURG - The ANC has cancelled all its January 8 events for 2021. The annual commemorations celebrate the party's anniversary. Instead, ANC President Cyril Ramaphosa, will deliver a virtual January 8 statement. READ: KZN ANC welcomes Gumede decision The party says it has met with Health Minister Dr. Zweli Mkhize, who indicated the rate of infections in all provinces would have increased by January. The ANC says it would have been inappropriate to forge ahead with the celebrations. The party says it has decided to uphold prescribed measures to minimise the spread and impact of the coronavirus. 